programme.title: Double Dream Hunt! Fallow Deer, Zebra & More at Ikamela Safaris!
programme.desc:
Join us as we continue our unforgettable hunting adventure at Ikamela Safaris in the Free State, South Africa!
• Mike Austin is on a mission to take down a Burchell's Zebra, an animal that's been on his bucket list since his first trip to Africa. But the hunt takes an unexpected turn when he crosses paths with a Fallow Deer Ram—a dream he never thought would come true! With a steady aim, Mike seizes the moment and makes a perfect shot.
• With the Fallow Deer in the salt, we get back on the Zebra's trail, tracking them across the farm. After an intense pursuit, Mike finally gets a shot opportunity at 250 yards—an incredible moment!
• Meanwhile, Johan Smit and PH Chris Snyman are out scouting when they bump into a massive Warthog boar. Johan makes a perfect 220-yard shot, securing another success for the team.
• Beulah Smit and Chris embark on an exciting stalk for a Gemsbuck, but they encounter an unexpected sight—White Rhinos resting under the trees. Respecting these majestic animals, they continue their search and later spot a stunning Waterbuck bull. Beulah delivers a heart shot, dropping it cleanly!
• On the final day, in the last hour of our trip, Beulah finally gets a chance at a troublesome Gemsbuck cow that has been causing issues on the property. She seals the deal, ending the hunt on a high note!
This episode is packed with action, breathtaking encounters, and unforgettable hunting moments. Don't miss it!

programme.title: Golden Moments in the Free State | Sable, Roan & Wildebeest Action!
programme.desc:
The Stover clan is back — and this time, they brought friends! Episode 5 of Season 5 takes us deep into the heart of our Free State concession for another unforgettable hunting adventure.
For Travis Koch, it was his first time in South Africa, and what a way to kick things off — with an adrenaline-pumping stalk on a Red Hartebeest that had all of us on edge. Dennis Stover came with one mission: a Roan bull. When we finally laid eyes on a true trophy, Dennis was locked in and ready for action. Larry Stover was on the trail of Black Wildebeest, and these ghosts of the plains sure made us work hard for a shot — it was a proper challenge from start to finish. Then there was Lance Stover, who was blessed with one of the rarest trophies of the Free State — a majestic Golden Gemsbuck bull. Just when we thought his day couldn't get any better, we stumbled upon another bucket-list animal… a Sable bull. One well-placed shot sealed an unforgettable evening. To top it off, Trey Wiseman, watching it all unfold, saw the bush offer him a fleeting but golden opportunity — and with nerves of steel, he harvested a Golden Wildebeest to wrap up an incredible hunt.
• Don't miss this action-packed episode full of wild moments, true camaraderie, and once-in-a-lifetime trophies — only on Huntech Pro!

programme.title: From Dream Hunts to Double Downs – African Magic Unfolds
programme.desc:
The action continues in Episode 6 of Season 5 of Huntech Pro as we follow the adventurous Stover clan on their unforgettable South African safari! This episode is packed with dream animals, quick decisions, perfect shots, and the kind of double action you won't believe until you see it.
Lance Stover kicks things off, going after a species that's been at the top of his wish list — the striking Red Lechwe. After a careful stalk, he connects with a beautiful ram.
Travis Koch had his eyes set on a Blue Wildebeest bull. We moved in close, he made the shot count, and the bull dropped in its tracks! But Travis wasn't done yet — later, he turned his focus to predators, and under the cover of darkness, dropped a beautiful Jackal after a successful call-in.
Dennis Stover originally wanted a Fallow Deer, but when a rare Black Fallow Deer appeared, he changed plans in an instant and made a great shot. Moments later, another Fallow Deer ram leapt from cover, and Trey was ready — making it the second double hunt of this trip!
Larry Stover had both Impala and Nyala on his list. While stalking Impala, we spotted a gorgeous Nyala bull, quickly shifted our focus, and Larry made the shot count.
This episode is the perfect example of how fast things can change in the bush — from quiet stalks to heart-pounding doubles, it's all happening right here.
Tune in now and experience the raw excitement of African hunting, the camaraderie of family, and the unforgettable moments that only Huntech Pro delivers.

programme.title: From 30 Yards to 713 Yards: Ultimate Accuracy
programme.desc:
Our three‑part adventure with the Stover clan crescendos in this action‑packed closer—five trophies, limitless excitement, and every shot told in living color.
The day opens with Greg Salmon and PH Andries Badenhorst glassing a black fallow deer ram on the rolling veld. A slow leopard‑crawl sets Greg into a rock‑steady rest; one smooth trigger pull anchors the dark‑antlered prize.
While Greg is tagging out, Dennis Stover and Johan Smit climb a windswept peak to stretch the .300 Win Mag. Johan ranges a Tsessebe cow at 713.5 yards, dials the "D.O.P.E." on the Hawke Frontier scope, and Dennis' bullet finds its mark—the cow folds instantly in the grass below.
Back in the thorn thickets, Travis Koch sets his sights on a hulking Watusi bull. With only 30 yards to spare, Travis shoulders the Ravin R26 crossbow tipped with a Thorn Crown 100 gr broadhead. The bolt flashes true; the giant horns stagger just 20 yards before coming to rest.
White is the color of the moment when Lance Stover whispers that he needs the snowy hide of a rare springbuck. A careful stalk leads to a slightly back first hit—but quick footwork and a flawless follow‑up shot turn persistence into a pristine ivory trophy.
Lady Luck caps the saga as Larry Stover and Andries spot a russet‑gold Lechwe ram. A final stalk closes the distance; Larry steadies, squeezes, and the regal ram crumples, sealing the clan's Free State grand slam.
Belly‑crawls, peak‑top dope‑dialing, and once‑in‑a‑lifetime trophies—Episode 7 is pure Huntech Pro storytelling. Subscribe, smash the ?, and tell us in the comments which moment had your heart racing!

programme.title: Non-Stop Hunting Action in the Northern Cape
programme.desc:
In this action-packed episode, the Huntech Pro team heads to Kudu Safari Africa, nestled in South Africa's vast Northern Cape province. Johan and Beulah Smit invite close friends and clients — Dennis, Larry, and Lance Stover — for a memorable hunt.
After flying from Johannesburg to Kimberley, the group is picked up by Johan Ludwick and PH Schalk van der Merwe and taken to the farm. The hunting action kicks off on the first afternoon when Johan makes a great shot on a beautiful Feral Goat, quickly followed by Dennis who also takes a stunning goat.
The following morning brings a stroke of luck for Lance, who drops a massive Waterbuck bull with a perfect shot. Johan returns to the field to pursue a true Northern Cape icon — the Afrikaner sheep. He spots a mature ram and makes another excellent shot. Inspired, Dennis steps up once more and takes a fine Afrikaner ram of his own.
That's all we have time for in this episode — but don't miss next week as the adventure at Kudu Safari Africa continues!
